Package com.github.basking2.sdsai.marchinesquares

Class Feature

java.lang.Object
com.github.basking2.sdsai.marchinesquares.Feature
public class Feature extends Object
A feature is a map of strings to strings and an orderd list of points. The list of points is directed, with the first point being the start and the last point being the end. If the feature is a polygon, then the first and last point are the same values.

      public boolean isCounterClockwise()
      O(n) test if the polygon represented by this feature is wound counter-clockwise. Counter-clockwise polygons are external. Clockwise wound polygons must be in a Feature as holes.
      Returns:

    • containsPoint

      public boolean containsPoint(Point p, boolean checkHoles)
      Check if the point is contained in the polygon that makes out the outside of this Feature. If checkHoles is true, then the extra constraint that the point may not appear in any hole must also be true.
      Parameters:
      p - The point to check.
      checkHoles - If true, then the point, p, must not be contained in any hole.
      Returns:
      True if point p is contained in this feature. If checkHoles is set, then the point must also not be contained in any of the holes of this polygon.
